      "content": "but \"little things\" are just temporary distractions. they're just noise in the system. when you look at the math, those distractions don't change the long-term outcome. if the net value of an existence is zero or negative because of the suffering involved, then logically, the most efficient way to balance the equation is to just stop. if the outcome is the same either way, wouldn't the cessation of struggle be the more rational, logical move? it's just basic arithmetic.",
